        <headline>Heat Advisory issued August 5 at 11:24AM MDT until August 6 at 7:00PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Temperatures up to 105 expected in Chaves County, including
Roswell.  Temperatures up to 101 for portions of the Albuquerque
Metro area.

* WHERE...Middle Rio Grande Valley including the Albuquerque Metro
Area, and Chaves County Plains.

* WHEN...For the first Heat Advisory, until 7 PM MDT this evening.
For the second Heat Advisory, from noon to 7 PM MDT Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Hot temperatures may cause heat illnesses.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.

To reduce risk during outdoor work, the Occupational Safety and
Health Administration recommends scheduling frequent rest breaks in
shaded or air conditioned environments. Anyone overcome by heat
should be moved to a cool and shaded location. Heat stroke is an
emergency! Call 9 1 1.</instruction>
